1
00:00:49,282 --> 00:00:51,079
CITY OF GOD

2
00:01:52,111 --> 00:01:57,879
Fuck, the chicken's got away!
Go after that chicken, man!

3
00:02:00,487 --> 00:02:02,682
Go on, for fuck's sake!

4
00:02:06,793 --> 00:02:08,920
Get that chicken!

5
00:02:22,876 --> 00:02:25,572
If it’s a good photo,
I'll get a job at the paper.

6
00:02:25,778 --> 00:02:27,939
-You think so, Rocket?
-Gotta take the risk.

7
00:02:28,147 --> 00:02:32,777
You'd risk your life
for a picture? Forget it!

8
00:02:33,353 --> 00:02:36,686
You think I want to meet up
with that motherfucking hood?

9
00:02:37,724 --> 00:02:41,592
Get that chicken, bro!

10
00:02:43,863 --> 00:02:46,889
Motherfucker! I told you
to grab that chicken!

11
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:49,227
Outta my way!

12
00:02:49,469 --> 00:02:51,437
Get that chicken!

13
00:03:11,057 --> 00:03:12,786
If Li’l Z' catches you,
he'll kill you.

14
00:03:14,661 --> 00:03:17,425
Yeah, well,
he's gotta find me first.

15
00:03:26,372 --> 00:03:30,001
Hey, kid! Get that chicken!
Get that chicken!

16
00:03:32,545 --> 00:03:33,876
Shit! The cops!

17
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:36,344
Don't fucking run off!

18
00:03:36,549 --> 00:03:38,346
Give me that.

19
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:43,421
Hey, Melonhead! You fucking fag!

20
00:03:44,490 --> 00:03:46,981
A picture could change
my life, but...

21
00:03:47,193 --> 00:03:50,458
in the City of God, if you
run away, they get you...

22
00:03:51,064 --> 00:03:54,522
...and if you stay, they get you too.
-They’re coming for us!

23
00:03:54,734 --> 00:03:57,396
It's been that way
ever since I was a kid...

24
00:04:00,139 --> 00:04:04,041
THE SIXTIES

25
00:04:10,984 --> 00:04:12,383
You’re useless, man!

26
00:04:12,585 --> 00:04:15,418
-Go get the ball!
-Fucking useless!

27
00:04:18,524 --> 00:04:19,718
Hey, kid!

28
00:04:19,926 --> 00:04:22,952
Give me the ball, I wanna play.

29
00:04:24,764 --> 00:04:28,291
-It’s not yours.
-You wanna mess with me?

30
00:04:28,501 --> 00:04:30,935
Fuck off.

31
00:04:31,137 --> 00:04:35,301
-What’s your name?
-Sorry, I forgot to introduce myself.

32
00:04:35,508 --> 00:04:38,033
-My name’s Rocket.
-Some advice, Rocket...

33
00:04:38,645 --> 00:04:41,808
Don’t let Li’l Dice
touch that ball. He sucks.

34
00:04:42,315 --> 00:04:44,306
-You lose, pal.
-Go, Shaggy!

35
00:04:44,517 --> 00:04:46,747
That's Shaggy.

36
00:04:46,953 --> 00:04:50,354
To tell the story of the City of God,
I have to start with him.

37
00:04:50,556 --> 00:04:52,581
8, 9, 10, 11...

38
00:04:53,860 --> 00:04:58,263
But in order to tell Shaggy's story, I
must tell the story of the Tender Trio.

39
00:04:58,464 --> 00:05:02,662
Well, Shaggy? The gas truck’s coming.
What are you fucking around for?

40
00:05:02,869 --> 00:05:04,803
You’re not gonna chicken out...

41
00:05:08,141 --> 00:05:11,668
THE STORY OF THE TENDER TRIO

42
00:05:17,350 --> 00:05:20,808
The notorious Tender Trio
was legendary in the City of God.

43
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:22,578
Shaggy...

44
00:05:23,289 --> 00:05:24,950
Clipper...

45
00:05:25,625 --> 00:05:27,092
and Goose.

46
00:05:29,028 --> 00:05:32,759
Tagging along were always
Li’l Dice and Benny...

47
00:05:32,965 --> 00:05:34,899
Shaggy's brother.

48
00:05:36,169 --> 00:05:39,832
I never had the courage
to follow my brother, Goose.

49
00:05:48,414 --> 00:05:50,382
Okay, let’s go.

50
00:05:51,050 --> 00:05:53,177
Come on, Goose.

51
00:05:53,453 --> 00:05:54,943
Let’s go!

52
00:06:04,931 --> 00:06:06,899
Stop! Stop!
Stop this fucker!

53
00:06:11,671 --> 00:06:15,505
Stop or I’ll shoot, motherfucker!

54
00:06:15,708 --> 00:06:18,006
Get out!

55
00:06:18,411 --> 00:06:23,474
Hurry up, asshole!
Gimme the money!

56
00:06:23,750 --> 00:06:26,344
Who wants gas?

57
00:06:34,927 --> 00:06:38,454
More! You wanna die for your
boss’ damn money?

58
00:06:38,664 --> 00:06:40,655
Shitloads of money here!

59
00:06:42,802 --> 00:06:45,100
You see, asshole?

60
00:06:46,105 --> 00:06:47,265
Asshole!

61
00:06:47,473 --> 00:06:49,441
Fuck! The cops!

62
00:06:52,779 --> 00:06:54,872
Let’s get outta here!

63
00:06:58,918 --> 00:07:02,649
Clear out! The place is
crawling with cops!

64
00:07:18,437 --> 00:07:21,668
-Shaggy!
-The ball, Goose, it’s yours!

65
00:07:31,584 --> 00:07:34,212
Back then, I thought
the guys in the Tender Trio...

66
00:07:34,420 --> 00:07:36,581
were the most dangerous hoods
in Rio.

67
00:07:36,789 --> 00:07:40,225
Here! Buy some new balls.

68
00:07:41,828 --> 00:07:45,229
But they were just amateurs.

69
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:52,093
-Even my brother, Goose.
-Rocket, give this money to dad.

70
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:56,572
But don’t tell him it’s from me.

71
00:07:56,776 --> 00:07:59,006
Okay?

72
00:07:59,212 --> 00:08:02,204
-Hey, Stringy!
-Yeah?

73
00:08:02,415 --> 00:08:04,679
Look how much I’ve got.

74
00:08:20,166 --> 00:08:24,899
We came to the City of God
hoping to find paradise.

75
00:08:25,104 --> 00:08:29,768
Many families were homeless
due to flooding...

76
00:08:29,976 --> 00:08:32,376
and acts of arson
in the ghettos.

77
00:08:32,578 --> 00:08:35,513
-A light post!
-We’ll have electricity!

78
00:08:35,715 --> 00:08:37,876
The bigwigs in government
didn't joke around.

79
00:08:38,084 --> 00:08:41,019
Homeless? Off to City of God!

80
00:08:41,220 --> 00:08:45,281
There was no electricity,
paved streets or transportation.

81
00:08:45,491 --> 00:08:48,688
But for the rich and powerful
our problems didn't matter.

82
00:08:48,928 --> 00:08:51,897
We were too far removed...

83
00:08:52,098 --> 00:08:54,566
from the picture postcard image
of Rio de Janeiro.

84
00:09:11,284 --> 00:09:14,014
Do you think I can become
a lifeguard one day?

85
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:16,051
I don’t know.

86
00:09:16,255 --> 00:09:19,122
Being a lifeguard is better
than a fishmonger.

87
00:09:19,325 --> 00:09:21,850
I don’t want to sell fish.
It stinks.

88
00:09:22,395 --> 00:09:24,761
-Are you insulting your father?
-No.

89
00:09:25,498 --> 00:09:28,467
So what do you want to be?

90
00:09:28,868 --> 00:09:30,495
I don’t know.

91
00:09:30,770 --> 00:09:34,297
-Not a hood or a policeman.
-Why not?

92
00:09:34,507 --> 00:09:36,668
I’m scared of getting shot.

93
00:09:41,147 --> 00:09:43,615
Put that thing away, kid.
Are you nuts?

94
00:09:43,816 --> 00:09:47,308
Pointing that gun at me?

95
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:50,751
Take it easy with the kid, Goose.
Li’l Dice is with me.

96
00:09:50,957 --> 00:09:53,790
Right, I'm a gangster too.

97
00:09:53,993 --> 00:09:56,621
-That gas truck didn't bring much.
-So what?

98
00:09:56,829 --> 00:10:00,458
-We rob gas trucks every day.
-One today, another tomorrow.

99
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:02,961
No, we need to rob
some rich guy’s house.

100
00:10:03,169 --> 00:10:05,603
That’s the only
way to get outta here.

101
00:10:05,805 --> 00:10:09,104
Hell, no. What you need
is to follow my plan.

102
00:10:09,308 --> 00:10:10,741
That’s it.

103
00:10:10,943 --> 00:10:15,039
The little fart’s getting
too big for his britches!

104
00:10:20,987 --> 00:10:24,354
He gets high and starts
talking bullshit.

105
00:10:24,557 --> 00:10:29,722
You two junkies aren't worth
half as much as that kid.

106
00:10:31,530 --> 00:10:34,590
What you got in mind, Li’l Dice?

107
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:39,396
To be a real hood you need
more than just a gun. You need ideas.

108
00:10:42,608 --> 00:10:44,701
And Li’l Dice had them.

109
00:10:45,878 --> 00:10:48,369
-Is that the motel?
-Yeah.

110
00:10:48,781 --> 00:10:53,514
We go in, grab the money and
get out. No killing, got that?

111
00:10:53,719 --> 00:10:57,052
-I need this.
-Don’t touch my gun, kid.

112
00:10:57,256 --> 00:10:58,450
Don’t ever do that again.

113
00:10:58,657 --> 00:11:00,249
-Don’t point at me.
-Fuck you.

114
00:11:00,459 --> 00:11:04,122
-Don’t point your finger at me!
-Stop acting like a baby!

115
00:11:04,830 --> 00:11:06,024
Here’s yours.

116
00:11:06,232 --> 00:11:08,632
-Awesome!
-Let’s go!

117
00:11:08,834 --> 00:11:11,359
-Not so fast!
-What?

118
00:11:11,570 --> 00:11:14,038
You stay here and keep watch.

119
00:11:14,306 --> 00:11:19,608
If the cops come, shoot that
window over there.

120
00:11:19,812 --> 00:11:22,713
-Why me? Let that dork do that.
-Look...

121
00:11:22,915 --> 00:11:28,114
I gave you this great plan, for free...
While that guy’s absolutely useless!

122
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:30,083
-You just had the idea.
-Exactly!

123
00:11:30,289 --> 00:11:32,780
You’re just a kid, remember?

124
00:11:33,392 --> 00:11:36,122
You cover us, okay?

125
00:11:37,129 --> 00:11:41,896
You’ll get your turn, so cool it.
Stop trying to rush things.

126
00:11:42,101 --> 00:11:44,592
You stay there.

127
00:11:48,407 --> 00:11:51,535
This is a hold-up, bitch.

128
00:11:54,647 --> 00:12:01,314
You should be studying or working.
You don't even look like hoodlums.

129
00:12:01,520 --> 00:12:05,513
Instead, you ought to be
working or studying, boy.

130
00:12:05,724 --> 00:12:08,591
Shut up!
What a pain in the ass!

131
00:12:09,562 --> 00:12:11,325
Okay, Clipper?

132
00:12:13,365 --> 00:12:14,764
Shall we go in?

133
00:12:20,106 --> 00:12:22,370
I didn't order anything.

134
00:12:22,575 --> 00:12:26,705
It’s on the house, sir.
Hand over the money!

135
00:12:26,912 --> 00:12:29,176
Keep calm, all I want
is your cash.

136
00:12:29,381 --> 00:12:30,973
-Don’t point that...
-Your wallet...

137
00:12:43,395 --> 00:12:44,919
Hey, man...

138
00:12:45,131 --> 00:12:47,326
What kind of whorehouse is this?

139
00:12:50,569 --> 00:12:53,129
-You from the church?
-Yes, brother.

140
00:12:56,208 --> 00:12:57,197
Give it to me!

141
00:12:59,411 --> 00:13:00,708
Slut!

142
00:13:00,946 --> 00:13:02,743
You're old, fat and flabby!

143
00:13:03,716 --> 00:13:06,014
Wanna take her place?

144
00:13:10,489 --> 00:13:12,650
What’s going on?

145
00:13:13,792 --> 00:13:16,488
-The cops! Let’s beat it!
-Let’s go!

146
00:13:21,634 --> 00:13:25,126
Take that car.
I'll go get Li’l Dice.

147
00:13:26,505 --> 00:13:28,939
Jesus, what a car!

148
00:13:34,880 --> 00:13:39,681
-Something fucked up. Li’l Dice’s gone.
-The cops are shooting, let’s go!

149
00:14:06,712 --> 00:14:09,112
Slow down! Hold on...

150
00:14:09,315 --> 00:14:12,148
-You said you knew how to drive.
-I do, so cool it!

151
00:14:12,351 --> 00:14:15,047
Turn! Watch out!

152
00:14:28,667 --> 00:14:30,430
You fucking asshole!

153
00:14:31,503 --> 00:14:34,199
Hey, I didn’t do it on purpose.

154
00:14:34,406 --> 00:14:38,035
No one saw anything.
So keep your mouths shut, understand?

155
00:14:41,814 --> 00:14:44,715
Hold on, I twisted my ankle.

156
00:14:44,917 --> 00:14:47,249
Goose fucked up his ankle.

157
00:14:47,453 --> 00:14:48,442
It fucking hurts.

158
00:14:48,654 --> 00:14:52,556
Take him into the woods.
I’ll shoot to distract the cops.

159
00:14:52,758 --> 00:14:55,090
-In God we trust.
-In God we trust.

160
00:14:59,999 --> 00:15:02,263
Pass me the telephone, Penguin.

161
00:15:02,468 --> 00:15:06,370
Shorty is another notorious guy
in the City of God.

162
00:15:06,572 --> 00:15:08,597
But it's not yet time
to tell his story.

163
00:15:10,475 --> 00:15:14,502
-It fucking hurts, Goose.
-Shut up.

164
00:15:15,214 --> 00:15:19,947
-Wait up...
-You sound like a damn sissy, man.

165
00:15:24,022 --> 00:15:27,287
-Give me your hand! Climb up!
-No one saw anything?

166
00:15:27,492 --> 00:15:32,327
How odd! A car crashes
into a bar and no one saw a thing.

167
00:15:32,531 --> 00:15:35,523
I suppose you didn’t see
anything either?

168
00:15:35,734 --> 00:15:39,465
As usual, no one saw,
no one knows.

169
00:15:40,205 --> 00:15:43,663
So what’s up, Shorty?

170
00:15:44,343 --> 00:15:47,107
They’re hiding in the woods.

171
00:15:48,113 --> 00:15:49,774
-Hello, Melonhead.
-How are you doing?

172
00:15:49,982 --> 00:15:53,418
I have this feeling that
they’re out in the woods.

173
00:15:53,652 --> 00:15:57,213
-The motherfuckers.
-They’re out in the woods.

174
00:15:57,990 --> 00:16:01,153
Felipe, lock up the car.
Rangel, come with me.

175
00:16:05,564 --> 00:16:08,829
I can’t see a thing.
How the hell can they see?

176
00:16:09,034 --> 00:16:11,468
Fucking jungle.

177
00:16:15,741 --> 00:16:19,802
-They stole a fortune at that motel.
-I know.

178
00:16:22,147 --> 00:16:24,809
What if we took the money?

179
00:16:25,317 --> 00:16:29,481
Are you crazy?
I’m not getting mixed up in that.

180
00:16:29,688 --> 00:16:32,248
I want to exterminate these guys.

181
00:16:32,457 --> 00:16:36,757
What? Since when is stealing from
niggers and thieves a crime?

182
00:16:37,095 --> 00:16:43,762
It won't be hard to nab them.
I have a stoolie in the City.

183
00:17:08,627 --> 00:17:15,294
-Did you hear those shots?
-If I catch one of them, I'll kill him.

184
00:17:27,045 --> 00:17:28,569
Maracana!

185
00:17:28,880 --> 00:17:31,075
Open the door.

186
00:17:33,352 --> 00:17:37,083
-What’s the matter?
-The cops are after me.

187
00:17:45,464 --> 00:17:46,863
Shaggy!

188
00:17:48,066 --> 00:17:50,933
-Shaggy!
-The cops are on my ass!

189
00:17:51,136 --> 00:17:54,367
-Hide me!
-Quick, come in.

190
00:18:02,214 --> 00:18:06,548
Shit... I thought the cops
would be down there all night.

191
00:18:07,886 --> 00:18:10,787
I had a vision, Goose.

192
00:18:11,523 --> 00:18:14,253
You been smoking something?

193
00:18:14,593 --> 00:18:17,426
-You've had a job, right?
-Yeah.

194
00:18:17,629 --> 00:18:19,688
What’s it like?
What do people say?

195
00:18:19,898 --> 00:18:22,025
I worked with my father.

196
00:18:22,234 --> 00:18:25,795
And fathers talk a lot of shit.

197
00:18:27,038 --> 00:18:31,065
You know what, Goose?
I'm getting out, I don't want to die.

198
00:18:31,276 --> 00:18:36,680
-This gangster’s life isn’t for me.
-Wait! The cops are still down there.

199
00:18:36,882 --> 00:18:39,544
I don’t give a shit.

200
00:18:41,720 --> 00:18:44,382
I'm going back to the church.

201
00:18:44,990 --> 00:18:47,083
He that dwells in the secret
place of the most High...

202
00:18:47,292 --> 00:18:50,659
shall abide under the shadow of
the Almighty. I will say of the Lord...

203
00:18:50,862 --> 00:18:55,128
He is my refuge and my fortress,
in Him will I trust.

204
00:18:55,333 --> 00:18:58,564
Fear not the terror by night,
nor the arrow that flies by day...

205
00:18:58,770 --> 00:19:02,797
nor the pestilence that walks
in darkness, nor the destruction...

206
00:19:03,008 --> 00:19:06,876
-Stop, motherfucker!
-Don’t move!

207
00:19:07,212 --> 00:19:10,648
Stop, or I’ll shoot!

208
00:19:12,284 --> 00:19:17,312
...shall abide under the shadow
of the Almighty.

209
00:19:17,522 --> 00:19:22,289
The hold-up at the motel went down
as the bloodiest in history.

210
00:19:22,494 --> 00:19:25,327
The destinies of the outlaws
then took different paths.

211
00:19:25,530 --> 00:19:28,966
I don’t think this guy
was involved in the heist.

212
00:19:29,167 --> 00:19:30,862
See here?

213
00:19:31,069 --> 00:19:36,473
-He’s a worker, not a hoodlum.
-I’ll make him one now.

214
00:19:39,744 --> 00:19:44,044
Destiny put Clipper
back into the hands of God.

215
00:19:45,584 --> 00:19:49,748
Shaggy was in Bernice's hands.

216
00:19:51,389 --> 00:19:54,916
And Goose was
in my father's hands.

217
00:19:55,126 --> 00:19:58,618
Why do you do these things?
You think I’m a fool?

218
00:19:58,830 --> 00:20:01,526
From now on,
you’ll work with me.

219
00:20:01,733 --> 00:20:05,897
Your younger brother
will keep an eye on you.

220
00:20:06,104 --> 00:20:08,095
You listen to me.

221
00:20:08,306 --> 00:20:12,675
If I catch you with money that
isn't yours, I'll kill you.

222
00:20:12,878 --> 00:20:18,748
That goes for you too. Get changed!
You start work immediately.

223
00:20:18,950 --> 00:20:24,718
Having a hood as a brother sucks.
You always end up footing the bill.

224
00:20:24,923 --> 00:20:29,189
Don’t worry.
Dad’s mad at me...

225
00:20:29,394 --> 00:20:33,797
but he’ll get over it.

226
00:20:36,935 --> 00:20:40,996
Give me that, Rocket. It’s not
for you. You have to study.

227
00:20:41,206 --> 00:20:44,539
-Getting shot doesn’t scare you?
-I’m a hood because I got no brain.

228
00:20:44,743 --> 00:20:48,577
But you’re smart.
You should study.

229
00:20:49,080 --> 00:20:52,379
I go to school because
I don’t like physical work.

230
00:20:52,918 --> 00:20:57,514
Promise me something... That you’ll
never touch this gun. Promise?

231
00:20:58,256 --> 00:21:00,315
Let’s shake.

232
00:21:01,826 --> 00:21:04,386
We’d better hurry.

233
00:21:05,664 --> 00:21:09,191
I’m gonna sell a lot of fish.
And don’t laugh.

234
00:21:09,401 --> 00:21:11,164
You grinned when I got slapped.

235
00:21:11,369 --> 00:21:13,269
-Who, me?
-I saw you.

236
00:21:41,232 --> 00:21:44,724
What is it, Shaggy?
Cat got your tongue?

237
00:21:44,936 --> 00:21:47,530
Your fidgeting behind me
makes me nervous.

238
00:21:47,739 --> 00:21:51,903
-I'm thinking of what to say to you.
-You’re thinking, as well?

239
00:21:52,110 --> 00:21:54,442
