00:42:07,956 --> 00:42:11,392
From Shaggy. You'll need it.

473
00:42:31,446 --> 00:42:34,074
From one hit to the next,
Li’l Dice grew up.

474
00:42:34,282 --> 00:42:38,685
At 18, he was the most
respected hood in the City of God.

475
00:42:38,887 --> 00:42:40,946
You’re of age now, watch out!

476
00:42:41,156 --> 00:42:44,455
He was one of the most
wanted robbers in Rio.

477
00:42:57,739 --> 00:42:59,400
Li’l Dice, how’s it going?

478
00:42:59,608 --> 00:43:03,237
Happy birthday.
I’m so glad you’ve turned 18...

479
00:43:03,445 --> 00:43:06,676
-Get lost, Tuba!
-Excuse me, amigo...

480
00:43:07,315 --> 00:43:09,374
Give me a beer!

481
00:43:09,584 --> 00:43:13,213
Didn’t you see me, prick?

482
00:43:13,421 --> 00:43:15,286
-Sorry, man.
-Up yours!

483
00:43:15,490 --> 00:43:18,857
The next time,
I’ll waste you, asshole!

484
00:43:20,262 --> 00:43:22,287
Fag!

485
00:43:22,631 --> 00:43:25,566
Li'l Dice was ready for anything.

486
00:43:25,767 --> 00:43:27,701
I wanna talk.

487
00:43:27,902 --> 00:43:30,894
-And he was itching to start.
-Who are the fattest cats here?

488
00:43:31,339 --> 00:43:35,571
-There are tons of them.
-Look at Jerry Adriani...

489
00:43:35,777 --> 00:43:39,873
gold chain, snazzy clothes.

490
00:43:40,081 --> 00:43:42,276
Look at Pereira
and the chick he’s with...

491
00:43:42,484 --> 00:43:46,352
-Bernice. She was my brother’s girl.
-Check out his car.

492
00:43:46,955 --> 00:43:51,085
Then there’s Blacky.
Covered in gold.

493
00:43:51,293 --> 00:43:53,955
Gold chain, gold watch...

494
00:43:54,162 --> 00:43:57,325
Look at Carrot, and his car.

495
00:43:57,532 --> 00:44:01,263
-They’re all dealers.
-They’re all fucking loaded.

496
00:44:01,469 --> 00:44:03,494
Hold-ups bring in chickenshit.

497
00:44:03,705 --> 00:44:06,503
-The big bucks are in drugs.
-I see.

498
00:44:06,708 --> 00:44:08,699
Especially in selling coke.

499
00:44:08,910 --> 00:44:11,174
-But you need money.
-Not really...

500
00:44:11,379 --> 00:44:15,076
We’ll kill these clowns
and take over their business.

501
00:44:15,283 --> 00:44:18,047
-When do we start?
-Now.

502
00:44:27,562 --> 00:44:31,521
Exu-the-Devil is the light
that shines forth.

503
00:44:31,733 --> 00:44:34,327
He brought you here.

504
00:44:34,536 --> 00:44:39,735
Why remain in the City of God
where God has forgotten you?

505
00:44:40,608 --> 00:44:45,011
I know what you want.
You want power.

506
00:44:45,213 --> 00:44:49,343
I have something which will
give it to you.

507
00:44:50,885 --> 00:44:55,379
To change your fate,
I give you my protector, boy.

508
00:44:55,590 --> 00:44:59,185
But you mustn't fornicate
with the amulet...

509
00:44:59,394 --> 00:45:01,862
otherwise...

510
00:45:02,931 --> 00:45:05,331
you’ll die.

511
00:45:05,834 --> 00:45:08,234
The boy is no longer called
Li’l Dice...

512
00:45:08,436 --> 00:45:10,427
but Li’l Z’.

513
00:45:10,638 --> 00:45:14,199
Li’l Z’ will grow up.

514
00:45:14,509 --> 00:45:18,309
You stick with me,
I’ll stick with you.

515
00:45:29,591 --> 00:45:33,049
Li’l Dice became Li'l Z'
and he began to kill.

516
00:45:34,095 --> 00:45:40,762
He started one morning,
taking over Jerry Adriani's racket.

517
00:45:41,970 --> 00:45:46,339
By that night, almost all
of the rackets in the ghetto were his.

518
00:45:46,541 --> 00:45:49,942
The only business he didn't
touch was Carrot's...

519
00:45:50,145 --> 00:45:54,104
since he was a friend of Benny's.
All that was left was the apartment...

520
00:45:54,315 --> 00:45:55,373
But that would be easy.

521
00:46:00,155 --> 00:46:03,215
Who is it?

522
00:46:09,964 --> 00:46:11,829
-Hey, Blacky.
-Fuck, Li’l Dice.

523
00:46:12,033 --> 00:46:18,165
-You show up like this at my place?
-Who said it was your place?

524
00:46:18,373 --> 00:46:20,000
-Something wrong, Li’l Dice?
-Li’l Dice, my ass.

525
00:46:20,208 --> 00:46:23,666
-My name is Li’l Z’ now.
-His name’s Li’l Z’, see?

526
00:46:23,878 --> 00:46:27,006
-You’re a goner, bastard.
-Don’t kill him. He understands.

527
00:46:27,215 --> 00:46:29,342
Right, Blacky?

528
00:46:29,551 --> 00:46:34,079
It’s all yours, I don’t want anything.
I don’t want no trouble, okay?

529
00:46:34,289 --> 00:46:37,417
I should have taken this chance
to avenge my brother's death.

530
00:46:39,294 --> 00:46:43,993
You’ll live, but you’ll
work for us. Understand?

531
00:46:44,199 --> 00:46:46,292
That's easy to say...

532
00:46:47,635 --> 00:46:50,832
-Where are you going?
-He’s clean, Li’l Z’.

533
00:46:51,406 --> 00:46:52,839
What’s your name, kid?

534
00:46:53,041 --> 00:46:56,841
-Rocket.
-He’s Goose’s brother.

535
00:46:57,045 --> 00:46:59,639
-Goose?
-The late Goose.

536
00:47:00,849 --> 00:47:03,113
Quick, kid. Run along.

537
00:47:03,318 --> 00:47:07,778
Tell everyone that this business
now belongs to Li’l Z’.

538
00:47:07,989 --> 00:47:11,891
And that we'll be selling coke.
Got that?

539
00:47:12,260 --> 00:47:13,989
Cocaine.

540
00:47:16,998 --> 00:47:19,933
-Where’s the turf?
-Over there, on the left.

541
00:47:20,134 --> 00:47:23,160
Selling drugs is like any
other business.

542
00:47:23,505 --> 00:47:25,405
The supplier
delivers the merchandise...

543
00:47:25,607 --> 00:47:28,337
which is then
packaged on the premises.

544
00:47:28,676 --> 00:47:32,476
It's done in an assembly line.

545
00:47:32,680 --> 00:47:34,739
Boring as hell...

546
00:47:35,216 --> 00:47:39,243
Pot is wrapped up in "lids".

547
00:47:39,521 --> 00:47:42,217
Cocaine is put into packets...

548
00:47:42,957 --> 00:47:47,189
and then into bundles
of 10 or 100.

549
00:47:47,562 --> 00:47:50,429
You can even make a career
in dealing drugs.

550
00:47:50,632 --> 00:47:54,466
The kids start out
as delivery boys.

551
00:47:54,736 --> 00:47:58,729
They're paid to run errands
and take messages.

552
00:47:59,474 --> 00:48:02,466
Then they become lookouts.
If the police arrive...

553
00:48:02,677 --> 00:48:05,510
the kites disappear
and everyone scrams.

554
00:48:06,781 --> 00:48:10,376
Later, you become a dealer
or a "vapor".

555
00:48:10,585 --> 00:48:13,679
When the heat's on, the
"vapor" quickly evaporates.

556
00:48:13,888 --> 00:48:18,018
Moving up the ladder,
you have the "soldier".

557
00:48:18,259 --> 00:48:21,854
And if the guy is good at math,
he can become a manager...

558
00:48:22,063 --> 00:48:25,521
the boss' right-hand man.

559
00:48:26,968 --> 00:48:30,904
The police receive their part
and don’t make trouble.

560
00:48:33,107 --> 00:48:35,701
Since Li’l Z' killed off
all of his enemies...

561
00:48:35,910 --> 00:48:40,870
there were no shoot-outs in the
City of God. You could drive there...

562
00:48:41,249 --> 00:48:44,776
The playboys felt safe
buying their drugs there.

563
00:48:46,220 --> 00:48:50,884
The City teemed with addicts
and Li’l Z' grew rich.

564
00:48:51,826 --> 00:48:54,124
-Is it okay?
-It’s a deal.

565
00:48:57,799 --> 00:49:01,826
-I can’t decide which to wear.
-This one’s cool.

566
00:49:02,670 --> 00:49:07,039
If dealing were legal, Li’l Z'
would have been man of the year.

567
00:49:10,311 --> 00:49:13,246
But things were risky for me.
I was afraid of him.

568
00:49:13,448 --> 00:49:17,646
-And he was everywhere.
-What a drag this guy is.

569
00:49:17,852 --> 00:49:22,983
Whenever I wanted to smoke a joint
I had to go see Carrot.

570
00:49:27,595 --> 00:49:30,496
Half a lid. Thanks.

571
00:49:31,633 --> 00:49:35,797
But it was worth it.
I only smoked with Angelica.

572
00:49:37,472 --> 00:49:40,339
She and Thiago had split up,
so I made my move.

573
00:49:40,541 --> 00:49:46,343
-I was about to win her over...
-These pictures are really great.

574
00:49:46,547 --> 00:49:50,142
-You think so?
-I look good here.

575
00:49:50,351 --> 00:49:53,115
-You look beautiful everywhere.
-I’m serious.

576
00:49:53,321 --> 00:49:54,310
Me too.

577
00:49:57,225 --> 00:50:02,458
A setting sun,
a deserted beach... a long kiss...

578
00:50:02,664 --> 00:50:05,497
I was sure this was it...

579
00:50:06,200 --> 00:50:08,691
But the Runts arrived.

580
00:50:09,270 --> 00:50:12,535
Can I have a toke?

581
00:50:18,112 --> 00:50:19,306
Here.

582
00:50:19,514 --> 00:50:23,712
I’m going. See you later.

583
00:50:25,586 --> 00:50:28,885
Hold on, Angelica.

584
00:50:29,090 --> 00:50:31,581
-Your joint, man.
-Keep it.

585
00:50:31,793 --> 00:50:34,125
What a cool guy.

586
00:50:37,098 --> 00:50:41,467
That was my first run
in with the Runts.

587
00:50:47,340 --> 00:50:50,400
-Steak and fries, Benny.
-Great! Here...

588
00:50:53,914 --> 00:50:59,853
-A tip for you.
-Really? Thanks.

589
00:51:00,053 --> 00:51:02,351
-Wanna eat something?
-No.

590
00:51:05,559 --> 00:51:09,757
-Wanna trade this watch?
-After Angelica left him...

591
00:51:09,963 --> 00:51:11,863
Thiago began snorting
more and more.

592
00:51:12,065 --> 00:51:15,159
-Is it your grandfather’s?
-No, my dad’s.

593
00:51:15,368 --> 00:51:19,668
When a guy is really hooked
he ends up in the hands of the dealer.

594
00:51:19,873 --> 00:51:22,000
-Two bags of ten.
-One of ten.

595
00:51:22,209 --> 00:51:26,305
-Okay, one bag.
-For Thiago, it was different.

596
00:51:26,513 --> 00:51:30,005
-Watch out!
-Sorry, godfather.

597
00:51:30,383 --> 00:51:33,181
Godfather, my ass.
Did I baptize your kids?

598
00:51:33,386 --> 00:51:36,412
-I’m sorry.
-Now beat it.

599
00:51:39,025 --> 00:51:43,018
Blacky, lend me your bike.

600
00:52:06,486 --> 00:52:08,750
Hey, wanna race?

601
00:52:08,955 --> 00:52:12,413
-Where to?
-Up to the highway.

602
00:52:13,026 --> 00:52:15,961
-Okay.
-Ready? Go!

603
00:52:38,351 --> 00:52:42,185
-Pretty tough, wasn’t it?
-Yeah, you’re good.

604
00:52:42,389 --> 00:52:44,721
Where’d you buy those sneakers?

605
00:52:44,924 --> 00:52:47,518
-Not far from here.
-The shirt, as well?

606
00:52:47,727 --> 00:52:50,059
-No, uptown.
-Cool.

607
00:52:50,263 --> 00:52:52,493
It’s a designer shirt.

608
00:52:52,699 --> 00:52:55,031
If I give you money
can you buy me one?

609
00:52:55,235 --> 00:52:57,897
Shorts and a shirt?

610
00:53:00,140 --> 00:53:02,438
Buy whatever you can.

611
00:53:05,111 --> 00:53:07,170
-What size are you?
-Measure me.

612
00:53:07,380 --> 00:53:10,315
-With what, man?
-Shit, with your hand.

613
00:53:11,818 --> 00:53:14,548
Shoe size? Turn around.

614
00:53:23,330 --> 00:53:28,290
-Hey, Benny!
-You got the digs?

615
00:53:31,304 --> 00:53:34,569
-Just one pair of pants?
-No, there’s more.

616
00:53:39,713 --> 00:53:40,975
-You like it?
-Yeah.

617
00:53:42,248 --> 00:53:44,580
There’s some change.

618
00:53:45,151 --> 00:53:48,086
-Keep it.
-Cool.

619
00:53:56,596 --> 00:53:59,190
This is Benny.

620
00:54:00,300 --> 00:54:03,895
-This is Rocket.
-Hi. I know him.

621
00:54:28,361 --> 00:54:31,023
I’ve become a playboy.

622
00:54:32,966 --> 00:54:37,096
Hey, gangsters, listen to this...

623
00:54:37,303 --> 00:54:39,134
Watch out...

624
00:54:39,339 --> 00:54:43,002
Groovies shake their asses
before laying a big one.

625
00:54:46,479 --> 00:54:48,208
Oh, yeah?

626
00:54:49,082 --> 00:54:51,778
Fuck off, you bastards!

627
00:54:54,120 --> 00:54:57,920
Making fun of me?

628
00:54:59,192 --> 00:55:01,387
Asshole!

629
00:55:16,309 --> 00:55:20,507
Benny, didn’t I tell you to shoot Carrot?
He’s endangering the ghetto.

630
00:55:20,713 --> 00:55:24,240
-Cool it. Go talk to him.
-I’m gonna kill that fucker.

631
00:55:24,451 --> 00:55:27,318
-Stop trying to wipe out everyone.
-I’m gonna kill him.

632
00:55:29,656 --> 00:55:32,648
Don’t worry, Angelica.
The guys in here are cool.

633
00:55:32,859 --> 00:55:35,453
Sure, I’m not worried.

634
00:55:35,929 --> 00:55:39,763
You gonna dance, Benny?
What about Carrot?

635
00:55:39,966 --> 00:55:44,027
Go on, buddy. Go talk to the guy.

636
00:55:44,237 --> 00:55:47,798
Benny was the coolest hood
in the City of God.

637
00:55:48,007 --> 00:55:51,170
He gave away pot,
paid for drinks.

638
00:55:51,678 --> 00:55:54,772
Li’l Z' was the opposite.
He had one obsession:

639
00:55:54,981 --> 00:55:56,949
to be the boss of the ghetto.

640
00:55:57,150 --> 00:56:00,415
He wanted an excuse to take over
Carrot's racket.

641
00:56:00,620 --> 00:56:02,247
-Hey, Carrot.
-What’s up?

642
00:56:02,455 --> 00:56:06,755
You shouldn’t let the Runts
do hold-ups in the ghetto.

643
00:56:07,327 --> 00:56:10,125
You look after your section,
I’ll look after mine.

644
00:56:10,330 --> 00:56:14,198
Got that? I'm gonna get a drink.

645
00:56:22,075 --> 00:56:26,978
-Hey, Rocket! How’s it going?
-Great.

646
00:56:27,180 --> 00:56:30,240
-Hey, Benny!
-How’s it going?

647
00:56:31,017 --> 00:56:33,986
-Hey, Thiago. How are you?
-Good.

648
00:56:35,054 --> 00:56:36,521
-May I?
-Sure...

649
00:56:36,723 --> 00:56:39,021
Wanna dance?

650
00:56:42,529 --> 00:56:45,987
-Is it okay at your place?
-No problem.

651
00:56:46,199 --> 00:56:49,862
My parents are out.
You’ll be all alone with her.

652
00:56:50,069 --> 00:56:54,472
-You can lose your virginity tonight.
-Not so loud, man!

653
00:56:54,674 --> 00:56:56,403
Everyone will hear.

654
00:56:57,644 --> 00:57:00,044
-You’re beautiful.
-Thank you.

655
00:57:00,246 --> 00:57:04,706
-Shit!
-Nothing’s happening.

656
00:57:11,925 --> 00:57:16,225
Look, man, I know the Runts
are associated with you.

657
00:57:16,429 --> 00:57:20,092
Think I'm a sucker, you little brat?
You want to take my racket?

658
00:57:20,300 --> 00:57:24,498
I want to talk to you
because you’re fucking useless.

659
00:57:24,704 --> 00:57:25,693
Get your hand away!

660
00:57:25,905 --> 00:57:28,931
The Runts are screwing up
our security, man.

661
00:57:29,142 --> 00:57:30,473
Give the baby his bottle.

662
00:57:30,677 --> 00:57:33,077
Carrot, just ask the kids
to cool it, okay?

663
00:57:33,279 --> 00:57:36,680
Carrot’s useless. He lets the Runts
do hold-ups in his section.

664
00:57:36,883 --> 00:57:39,818
The police come around and
that’s bad for business.

665
00:57:40,086 --> 00:57:43,681
I’ll do it only because
I like you.

666
00:57:44,023 --> 00:57:45,684
But you need to change
that baby's diapers.

667
00:57:45,892 --> 00:57:49,726
I’ll show you who’s the baby...

668
00:57:49,929 --> 00:57:55,424
Tell the kids that in my ghetto
no one robs or rapes!

669
00:57:55,635 --> 00:57:57,102
No wonder you’re "Little" Z’!

670
00:58:00,273 --> 00:58:05,210
The Runts were kids who didn't
respect the laws of the ghetto.

671
00:58:05,411 --> 00:58:08,869
They would mug residents,
hold up bakeries...

672
00:58:09,082 --> 00:58:11,277
especially in Carrot's section.

673
00:58:14,220 --> 00:58:17,781
What are you doing?

674
00:58:19,559 --> 00:58:24,053
-You rob me all the time!
-But they didn't know...

675
00:58:24,263 --> 00:58:26,595
that the City had a boss now.

676
00:58:28,468 --> 00:58:30,493
THANK YOU FOR CHOOSING US

677
00:58:30,703 --> 00:58:34,537
The City had become
much safer for residents.

678
00:58:35,875 --> 00:58:38,742
There were hardly
any hold-ups now.

679
00:58:38,978 --> 00:58:40,275
You just had to go see Li’l Z'.

680
00:58:40,480 --> 00:58:43,608
-Let’s go.
-Don’t hurt the Runts.

681
00:58:43,816 --> 00:58:46,717
I won’t touch them.

682
00:58:50,390 --> 00:58:52,358
-Hi, Steak.
-How’s it going, Li’l Z’?

683
00:58:52,558 --> 00:58:55,254
-Wanna take a walk, Steak?
-With you? Hold on...

684
00:58:57,697 --> 00:59:00,689
Mom, I’m going out with
my friends.

685
00:59:13,146 --> 00:59:15,808
That’s the best chicken
I ever ate.

686
00:59:16,282 --> 00:59:20,343
-The old guy was scared shitless.
-Feeling sorry for him?

687
00:59:20,553 --> 00:59:23,579
You’re crazy, man!

688
00:59:31,998 --> 00:59:34,865
Why not stick up
a bank or a supermarket?

689
00:59:35,068 --> 00:59:39,505
-Peanuts. Drugs are where it’s at.
-Yeah, selling drugs.

690
00:59:39,706 --> 00:59:46,009
But you have to start out as a delivery
boy. You wanna be a delivery boy?

691
00:59:46,212 --> 00:59:51,445
It’s a rip off.
It takes a long time to move up.

692
00:59:51,751 --> 00:59:56,085
You have to wait till an older guy
gets killed to move up.

693
00:59:56,322 --> 00:59:59,485
I don't wanna wait till some guy
croaks. I'm gonna do what Li’l Z' did.

694
00:59:59,692 --> 01:00:02,388
I'm gonna wipe them all out.

695
01:00:02,595 --> 01:00:05,428
Talking about me, kid?
The boss is here.

696
01:00:09,535 --> 01:00:11,093
Come back, you brat!

697
01:00:15,475 --> 01:00:22,142
-They’re quick, those kids.
-They run fast.

698
01:00:23,382 --> 01:00:26,283
They’re all gone except you.
Any others?

699
01:00:33,860 --> 01:00:36,522
You’re gonna pay
for the ones that escaped.

700
01:00:36,729 --> 01:00:40,893
You choose. Shall I shoot you
in the hand or foot?

701
01:00:41,501 --> 01:00:43,401
Come on, choose!

702
01:00:43,603 --> 01:00:46,367
Hand or foot?

703
01:00:48,908 --> 01:00:51,638
Choose, for fuck's sake!

704
01:00:59,385 --> 01:01:02,513
-Hand.
-The little hand, eh?

705
01:01:11,397 --> 01:01:13,490
Cool.

706
01:01:14,767 --> 01:01:19,170
Hey, Steak’n’fries,
