Let’s go!

941
01:25:26,717 --> 01:25:30,653
Gerson...

942
01:25:30,854 --> 01:25:34,449
That bastard killed my brother.

943
01:25:42,399 --> 01:25:45,163
I can’t let that go.

944
01:26:00,384 --> 01:26:02,511
-Want a gun?
-My son...

945
01:26:02,719 --> 01:26:06,120
Calm down, mom.

946
01:26:06,957 --> 01:26:09,824
Please, mom...

947
01:26:18,635 --> 01:26:22,298
Do it right, asshole.

948
01:26:22,506 --> 01:26:26,237
-There’s no other way.
-How’d I let that loser hit me?

949
01:26:26,443 --> 01:26:28,911
Shit, that’s some hole.

950
01:26:58,642 --> 01:27:01,634
-It’s as if we were brothers.
-Shut up.

951
01:27:01,845 --> 01:27:06,373
Both of us hurt in the arm.
You by one brother, me the other.

952
01:27:06,583 --> 01:27:10,383
It would be really funny
if we were brothers.

953
01:27:10,587 --> 01:27:16,685
That Knockout Ned's not bad, eh?
He came out of nowhere.

954
01:27:17,461 --> 01:27:21,090
Shut up, Tuba!
You're a fucking pain!

955
01:27:28,639 --> 01:27:32,803
It was as if the City of God
had suddenly found a hero.

956
01:27:33,010 --> 01:27:35,171
God bless you, son.

957
01:27:35,379 --> 01:27:38,644
That kid was just asking
to be killed.

958
01:27:38,849 --> 01:27:41,545
Well done.

959
01:27:41,752 --> 01:27:44,983
You did a good job.

960
01:27:45,188 --> 01:27:48,817
You’d better go hide.

961
01:27:51,428 --> 01:27:54,693
I thought Knockout Ned
would start a revolution here.

962
01:27:54,898 --> 01:27:57,662
But God had other plans.

963
01:27:57,968 --> 01:28:01,563
Steak,
where are all the dealers?

964
01:28:01,772 --> 01:28:05,037
They’re hiding.
Li’l Z’ is in a bad mood.

965
01:28:05,242 --> 01:28:08,973
They get us hooked and then
they go off and hide.

966
01:28:09,179 --> 01:28:12,410
Do me a favor. Go get some
nose candy for me.

967
01:28:12,616 --> 01:28:14,015
I’ll try.

968
01:28:14,217 --> 01:28:17,675
Tell them it’s for Thiago,
to keep my buzz going.

969
01:28:38,274 --> 01:28:43,644
Steak’n’fries,
go to Carrot’s and tell him...

970
01:28:43,846 --> 01:28:49,216
Li’l Z' says that if you kill
Knockout, he’ll leave you alone.

971
01:28:49,852 --> 01:28:52,719
Hey, Knockout Ned.
Did you hear that?

972
01:28:52,922 --> 01:28:55,584
Grab the kid!

973
01:28:57,760 --> 01:29:03,426
You heard the boy? If you don't
stick with us, you're dead.

974
01:29:03,633 --> 01:29:06,898
I think you should join us.
We'll be partners.

975
01:29:07,570 --> 01:29:10,505
Drugs aren't my thing.

976
01:29:10,707 --> 01:29:12,834
This is just something
between me and him.

977
01:29:13,042 --> 01:29:17,706
Those guys aren’t worth shit.

978
01:29:17,914 --> 01:29:21,509
They'll do anything for power.

979
01:29:21,718 --> 01:29:24,050
Like that kid.

980
01:29:24,253 --> 01:29:28,383
They're all robots,
like this punk here.

981
01:29:28,591 --> 01:29:30,855
What’s in your head, kid?

982
01:29:31,060 --> 01:29:33,494
Can't you see you're
wrecking your life...

983
01:29:33,696 --> 01:29:37,928
with that maniac and a bunch
of trigger-happy fools?

984
01:29:39,402 --> 01:29:46,069
-Are you crazy? You’re just a kid.
-A kid? I smoke, snort...

985
01:29:46,275 --> 01:29:49,574
I’ve killed and robbed.
I’m a man.

986
01:29:49,779 --> 01:29:52,304
Shit, you have no idea!

987
01:29:52,515 --> 01:29:55,746
He’s attached to his gang.
You should join up with us.

988
01:29:55,952 --> 01:30:00,821
-Shall we kill him?
-Steak, we're going to grind you.

989
01:30:02,425 --> 01:30:06,657
-Okay, I accept.
-Great!

990
01:30:06,863 --> 01:30:10,959
Tell your boss that Knockout Ned
and Carrot are now in command.

991
01:30:11,167 --> 01:30:17,367
But on one condition:
no killing of innocent people.

992
01:30:19,008 --> 01:30:21,602
I can't accept that, understand?

993
01:30:21,811 --> 01:30:26,475
Okay, no innocent people.

994
01:30:27,884 --> 01:30:32,821
Steak fucked up!

995
01:30:44,500 --> 01:30:47,094
-Have you a gun for me?
-No...

996
01:30:47,303 --> 01:30:50,704
but we can hold up
a gun store.

997
01:30:50,907 --> 01:30:52,966
That’s no problem.

998
01:30:53,176 --> 01:30:56,771
I don’t want to hold up anything.
I’m not a hoodlum.

999
01:30:56,979 --> 01:31:00,176
This is a personal affair
between me and him, okay?

1000
01:31:00,850 --> 01:31:03,114
I’m not a hoodlum.

1001
01:31:05,488 --> 01:31:07,456
He raped your chick...

1002
01:31:07,657 --> 01:31:11,491
killed your uncle and brother,
gunned your house...

1003
01:31:11,694 --> 01:31:15,061
and you killed one of his guys.

1004
01:31:19,401 --> 01:31:23,030
If you’re not a hood,
then get out.

1005
01:31:28,110 --> 01:31:32,547
THE STORY OF KNOCKOUT NED

1006
01:31:33,715 --> 01:31:36,206
This is a hold-up!

1007
01:31:44,259 --> 01:31:47,888
-The first time...
-Where are the revolvers?

1008
01:31:48,096 --> 01:31:51,725
...Knockout Ned saved a salesclerk
from being shot by Carrot.

1009
01:31:51,933 --> 01:31:56,336
We said no killing!

1010
01:31:56,538 --> 01:31:58,335
That’s the rule.

1011
01:31:59,574 --> 01:32:04,807
We want the boss’ money. Everyone
keep calm. Open the cash register!

1012
01:32:05,013 --> 01:32:07,914
You want us to go?
We do too.

1013
01:32:08,116 --> 01:32:10,550
So hurry up!

1014
01:32:11,787 --> 01:32:14,187
-Look at the ground!
-The second time...

1015
01:32:14,389 --> 01:32:16,323
Carrot saved
Knockout Ned's life.

1016
01:32:19,094 --> 01:32:22,222
Ned learned that there's
an exception to every rule.

1017
01:32:22,864 --> 01:32:25,196
Exception to the rule.

1018
01:32:25,400 --> 01:32:28,494
-Are you the manager?
-Yes.

1019
01:32:28,703 --> 01:32:32,696
This is a hold-up.
Everyone on the ground!

1020
01:32:32,908 --> 01:32:34,933
On the ground!

1021
01:32:35,143 --> 01:32:39,375
Give me the money!

1022
01:32:42,317 --> 01:32:44,547
I’m not kidding.

1023
01:32:44,753 --> 01:32:46,983
The first person who moves
is dead!

1024
01:32:47,389 --> 01:32:51,018
The third time, the exception
becomes the rule.

1025
01:33:06,808 --> 01:33:11,177
Carrot and Knockout Ned
prepared to face Li’l Z'.

1026
01:33:11,379 --> 01:33:14,177
Carrot could protect his
business.

1027
01:33:14,449 --> 01:33:16,212
Knockout Ned...

1028
01:33:16,418 --> 01:33:19,353
the best marksman in his battalion,
wanted revenge.

1029
01:33:19,554 --> 01:33:23,752
First, the Italians.
This is a 9 mm.

1030
01:33:24,493 --> 01:33:26,723
-Let me see.
-Not bad, eh?

1031
01:33:26,928 --> 01:33:31,627
-The sight isn’t well-aligned.
-I’ll give you a good price.

1032
01:33:32,434 --> 01:33:34,425
The 12 mm, the "hand job".

1033
01:33:35,070 --> 01:33:36,298
See why?

1034
01:33:36,505 --> 01:33:39,565
An Uzi, 9 mm. It’s Israeli.

1035
01:33:39,774 --> 01:33:42,641
-The star of David.
-Jewish.

1036
01:33:42,844 --> 01:33:44,209
I want a 30-06.

1037
01:33:44,679 --> 01:33:47,045
Now we can start having fun.

1038
01:33:47,249 --> 01:33:51,583
The war’s on.
Let’s start with a prayer.

1039
01:33:51,953 --> 01:33:56,049
Our Father who art in heaven
hallowed be our name...

1040
01:33:56,258 --> 01:34:00,422
Our will be done...

1041
01:34:00,962 --> 01:34:03,453
On earth as it is in heaven...

1042
01:34:16,711 --> 01:34:18,770
Hoodlums have guns,
but can't shoot.

1043
01:34:19,080 --> 01:34:23,107
One bullet from Knockout Ned
was worth ten from Li’l Z”s gang.

1044
01:34:23,318 --> 01:34:27,448
Li’l Z' couldn't take it.
He counter-attacked.

1045
01:34:30,091 --> 01:34:34,323
The ghetto had been a purgatory,
now it was hell.

1046
01:34:38,266 --> 01:34:43,966
I decided to get out.
That's how I became a reporter.

1047
01:34:44,839 --> 01:34:47,273
Great photo!

1048
01:34:47,475 --> 01:34:49,943
I bet it’s by Rogerio Reis.

1049
01:34:50,512 --> 01:34:53,345
What did I tell you?

1050
01:34:53,548 --> 01:34:55,743
Like any pro...

1051
01:34:55,951 --> 01:34:59,387
I started at the bottom,
way down at the bottom.

1052
01:34:59,588 --> 01:35:03,046
Without knowing what awaited me.

1053
01:35:04,693 --> 01:35:07,662
Instead of going home
I’d go over to the paper.

1054
01:35:07,862 --> 01:35:11,229
A guy from the City of God
worked in the lab.

1055
01:35:11,433 --> 01:35:14,300
Check this out.

1056
01:35:14,502 --> 01:35:18,563
He helped me move closer to
what I loved most in life.

1057
01:35:18,773 --> 01:35:20,400
-Hi, Rogerio.
-How are you, Pierre?

1058
01:35:20,609 --> 01:35:23,237
This is Rocket.
He’s a photographer.

1059
01:35:23,445 --> 01:35:24,605
Hello, Rocket.

1060
01:35:24,813 --> 01:35:27,077
-He’s a fan of yours.
-Really?

1061
01:35:27,282 --> 01:35:28,909
You have good taste, Rocket!

1062
01:35:29,117 --> 01:35:32,211
-Well, I’m done. I’m off.
-See you.

1063
01:35:32,420 --> 01:35:35,082
What a cool guy!

1064
01:35:35,890 --> 01:35:38,984
What should have been
a swift revenge...

1065
01:35:39,194 --> 01:35:41,685
turned into an all-out war.

1066
01:35:46,801 --> 01:35:49,031
The City of God was divided.

1067
01:35:49,237 --> 01:35:53,037
You couldn't go from one
section to the other.

1068
01:35:53,241 --> 01:35:55,471
Not even to visit a relative.

1069
01:35:55,677 --> 01:35:59,408
The cops considered anyone
living in the ghetto a hoodlum.

1070
01:35:59,614 --> 01:36:03,050
People got used to living
in Vietnam.

1071
01:36:07,255 --> 01:36:12,215
And more and more volunteers
kept signing up to die.

1072
01:36:12,427 --> 01:36:13,416
This kid...

1073
01:36:13,628 --> 01:36:16,358
-What do you want?
-A boy from Carrot’s gang punched me.

1074
01:36:16,898 --> 01:36:18,263
The war was
an excuse for everything.

1075
01:36:18,667 --> 01:36:20,635
One of Li’l Z”s soldiers
kicked me.

1076
01:36:22,671 --> 01:36:24,696
Take this.22.

1077
01:36:26,508 --> 01:36:28,976
The jerk who raped my sister is
with Carrot.

1078
01:36:29,177 --> 01:36:30,576
Li’l Z’ evicted my family.

1079
01:36:31,613 --> 01:36:33,240
Kill... Be respected.

1080
01:36:45,627 --> 01:36:51,088
-I’m Thiago, a friend of Benny’s.
-Can you read? Can you add?

1081
01:36:51,299 --> 01:36:56,737
-I’m pretty good in business.
-Okay, get to work.

1082
01:36:57,238 --> 01:37:00,605
-What do you want?
-To get my father’s murderer.

1083
01:37:01,009 --> 01:37:03,773
-What’s your name?
-My name’s Otto.

1084
01:37:09,217 --> 01:37:11,185
What’s the matter?

1085
01:37:11,386 --> 01:37:15,345
-He’s a worker.
-But he wants a gun.

1086
01:37:16,091 --> 01:37:18,753
He won’t last a week.

1087
01:37:29,771 --> 01:37:34,606
A year later, no one
remembered how it had all begun.

1088
01:37:34,809 --> 01:37:36,140
Take that!

1089
01:37:38,947 --> 01:37:44,886
For both sides, the aim was to take
over the enemy's business in order...

1090
01:37:45,086 --> 01:37:48,613
to buy more guns and take over
more businesses.

1091
01:38:10,445 --> 01:38:13,642
I smoke, snort,
I’ve killed and robbed.

1092
01:38:13,848 --> 01:38:16,180
I’m a man.

1093
01:38:37,839 --> 01:38:42,867
The media started taking an interest.
The police had to intervene.

1094
01:38:56,825 --> 01:39:01,228
A gang leader, from the City of God,
was arrested today.

1095
01:39:01,429 --> 01:39:03,158
Manuel Machado,
a.k.a. Knockout Ned...

1096
01:39:03,364 --> 01:39:06,765
was hospitalized after being
wounded by Li’l Z”s gang.

1097
01:39:06,968 --> 01:39:09,198
Our reporter interviewed him.

1098
01:39:09,404 --> 01:39:13,363
-Is the war still going on?
-It's still going on.

1099
01:39:13,641 --> 01:39:18,169
-Have many people died?
-Many have died.

1100
01:39:18,379 --> 01:39:20,506
Mostly innocent people.

1101
01:39:20,715 --> 01:39:24,082
Just knowing me is enough...

1102
01:39:24,285 --> 01:39:29,018
to get you killed by Li’l Z'.

1103
01:39:29,224 --> 01:39:32,591
-The police don’t go in there?
-They go after me, not him.

1104
01:39:32,794 --> 01:39:39,131
I’ve been in jail, while he goes
on killing undisturbed.

1105
01:39:39,334 --> 01:39:41,427
And they don’t arrest him.

1106
01:39:41,636 --> 01:39:43,934
Knockout Ned says
the war will continue.

1107
01:39:44,138 --> 01:39:49,735
Police Chief Guedes has promised
to arrest both of the gangs.

1108
01:39:58,219 --> 01:39:59,948
Motherfucker!

1109
01:40:00,154 --> 01:40:03,715
I’m the boss here, but he gets
his picture in the paper!

1110
01:40:03,925 --> 01:40:07,486
-Have you found mine?
-Just Knockout Ned’s.

1111
01:40:07,695 --> 01:40:09,162
Keep looking.

1112
01:40:09,564 --> 01:40:12,294
At least my name’s
got to be in there.

1113
01:40:12,500 --> 01:40:14,195
-There’s nothing.
-Can you read?

1114
01:40:14,402 --> 01:40:16,836
Just the pictures.

1115
01:40:17,805 --> 01:40:19,864
Nothing.

1116
01:40:20,074 --> 01:40:23,168
Hey, what the fuck are you doing?

1117
01:40:23,378 --> 01:40:28,509
-It’s just the want ads.
-I don’t care, read everything!

1118
01:40:28,716 --> 01:40:32,880
-But there aren’t any articles.
-Want a bullet in your head?

1119
01:40:34,889 --> 01:40:38,381
Gotta show them who’s boss here.

1120
01:40:43,431 --> 01:40:47,128
-Give me the camera!
-No way!

1121
01:40:49,671 --> 01:40:52,003
Take my picture, man.

1122
01:40:52,607 --> 01:40:55,337
I can’t work it.

1123
01:40:55,543 --> 01:40:57,238
Go ahead.

1124
01:40:57,612 --> 01:41:02,174
-I’ll hold the Beretta.
-Let me try...

1125
01:41:02,817 --> 01:41:05,513
Back off...

1126
01:41:05,720 --> 01:41:09,986
-There’s no click.
-What a bunch of bozos!

1127
01:41:10,491 --> 01:41:13,255
I’m fucked with you guys.

1128
01:41:15,330 --> 01:41:17,890
I have an idea.

1129
01:41:18,099 --> 01:41:22,627
I’ll go get a guy I know.
Hang loose.

1130
01:41:23,504 --> 01:41:27,406
-Here he is.
-Take the camera.

1131
01:41:28,109 --> 01:41:30,543
Well, kid?

1132
01:41:31,612 --> 01:41:37,016
Aren’t you a photographer?
Make the camerawork. We can’t do it.

1133
01:41:38,820 --> 01:41:40,617
Take our picture.

1134
01:41:45,560 --> 01:41:49,360
-You fucking broke it.
-It wasn’t me.

1135
01:41:49,931 --> 01:41:51,626
I found it.

1136
01:41:53,468 --> 01:41:55,629
It has to be wound.

1137
01:42:00,074 --> 01:42:03,066
-What’s your name?
-Rocket.

1138
01:42:03,444 --> 01:42:07,380
-Another picture, Rocket.
-How about two rows?

1139
01:42:07,582 --> 01:42:12,485
-What?
-Two rows. Everyone with their guns.

1140
01:42:13,254 --> 01:42:17,281
-You’re outside, for Christ’s sake!
-Talk to him nicely, kid.

1141
01:42:17,492 --> 01:42:19,426
Sorry. Move in, please.

1142
01:42:21,929 --> 01:42:24,397
Another one.

1143
01:42:28,770 --> 01:42:31,068
-I think the roll’s finished.
-Then show us the pictures.

1144
01:42:31,272 --> 01:42:34,139
-They have to be developed.
-Developed?

1145
01:42:35,376 --> 01:42:37,037
How much is it?

1146
01:42:37,645 --> 01:42:42,048
Take this money.
And bring back the pictures.

1147
01:42:42,250 --> 01:42:47,517
-I have to remove the film.
-Keep the camera.

1148
01:42:48,022 --> 01:42:52,425
Benny wanted to give it to you,
didn’t he? So, it’s yours...

1149
01:42:52,627 --> 01:42:54,458
Thanks.

1150
01:42:56,397 --> 01:43:00,595
Don’t forget the pictures.
The photos, Rocket!

1151
01:43:11,679 --> 01:43:14,011
-Pierre!
-What?

1152
01:43:14,415 --> 01:43:17,782
Can you develop this for me?

1153
01:43:18,486 --> 01:43:21,944
I can’t, Rocket.
I could get into trouble.

1154
01:43:22,156 --> 01:43:24,886
It’s only for the paper’s reporters.
I could risk my job.

1155
01:43:25,093 --> 01:43:26,583
-Pierre?
-Yes, Rogerio?

1156
01:43:26,794 --> 01:43:31,424
Develop these for me.
This one too, okay?

1157
01:43:31,833 --> 01:43:34,199
I’m going to lunch.

1158
01:43:34,402 --> 01:43:38,498
You’re lucky. What size?

1159
01:43:38,706 --> 01:43:42,107
-What?
-For the enlargement, what size?

1160
01:43:42,577 --> 01:43:46,377
Well... Whatever you think is best.

1161
01:44:06,167 --> 01:44:08,294
-Here.
-Thanks.

1162
01:44:12,173 --> 01:44:14,835
I’m in deep shit now.

1163
01:44:16,744 --> 01:44:19,269
I’m as good as dead.

1164
01:44:30,525 --> 01:44:32,618
Someone had signed
my death sentence.

1165
01:44:32,827 --> 01:44:36,285
I wanted to bash the jerk's face in.

1166
01:44:41,969 --> 01:44:45,598
Are you Marina?
Because of you I’m dead.

1167
01:44:45,806 --> 01:44:47,933
You stole my photos.

1168
01:44:48,142 --> 01:44:52,010
Dead? Stole? What do you mean?
Not so loud.

1169
01:44:53,314 --> 01:44:55,839
Not so loud?
I’ll be killed because of you.

1170
01:44:56,050 --> 01:44:58,610
You were gone,
your photos were in the lab.

1171
01:44:58,819 --> 01:45:01,652
There's nothing I can do.
The photos in our lab...

1172
01:45:01,856 --> 01:45:04,654
are photos to be published
in the paper.

1173
01:45:04,859 --> 01:45:08,124
I saw the photos,
I published them.

1174
01:45:08,329 --> 01:45:10,729
-You stole them.
-I did not. Here they are.

1175
01:45:10,932 --> 01:45:15,301
-Give them to me.
-Just a second.

1176
01:45:15,503 --> 01:45:18,631
Here are your photos.

1177
01:45:18,839 --> 01:45:22,605
-Are there any others?
